	<phrase id="4" desc="">
		<original>
			Which is the more popular term — "Disciple" or "Christian?" The word "Christian" only appears three times in the New Testament. It is the name those in the world gave the disciples, seven years after the church began. (Acts 11:19-26). The word "Disciple" occurs over 270 times in the New Testament.
		</original>
		<translated>
			哪个更常见名称 - 门徒或基督徒？基督徒在新约中只出现三次。这是当时人们在教会开始七年后给门徒的绰号（使徒行传 11:19-26）。 在新约中，“门徒”一词出现了270多次。
		</translated>
		<change bold="true" italic="false" modal="true" scripturekey="acts-11-19-26">
			<original>
				Acts 11:19-26
			</original>
			<translated>
				使徒行传 11:19-26
			</translated>
		</change>
	</phrase>

	<phrase id="5" desc="">
		<original>
			SAVED = CHRISTIAN = DISCIPLE
		</original>
		<translated>
			得救 = 基督徒 = 门徒
		</translated>
	</phrase>

	<phrase id="6" desc="">
		<original>
			Jesus came to make disciples. Only baptized disciples will be saved.
		</original>
		<translated>
			耶稣来使人们作他的门徒。只有受洗后的门徒才会得救。
		</translated>
	</phrase>

